title.narrative: South Sudan Health Pooled Fund - Programme Resource

description.narrative: This activity (South Sudan Health Pooled Fund - Programme Resource) is a component of South Sudan Health Pooled Fund II reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £53,458,632. This component benefits South Sudan, and works in the following sector(s): Health policy and administrative management, Basic health care, Health education, Public sector policy and administrative management. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited, Regional Service Organisation Northern Africa (RSO NAF), Embassy of the Kingdom of the Netherlands, Accra, Ghana. The start date is 17-04-2012 and the end date is 31-03-2017.
